rComments: From his intense look to his thic sweater vests, there is nothing to not love. He is a caring prof who is always ready to answer students questions and takes time to make sure you understand something. Personally I felt really encouraged to speak/try and participate in class. Participation goes a long way. Tests are harder than expected. REVIEW.

If aliens were to come to earth and ask to see a representation of the most normal man, Fernandez Pelaez would be my candidate. He's middle-aged, balding, married, reads the newspaper, enjoys long walks, etc. He grades normally and tries to be engaging, only succeeding a normal amount of the time. He does mark you down a lot for skipping class.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: The man comes off as very unapproachable. Shy, timid, tries to avoid taking questions from students during / after class. He's more than comfortable taking questions via email. Lectures were regurgitated verbatim of the text, almost uses the text like a crutch of sorts. On the positive side, he does have an upbeat and likable personality.
